<topic xml:lang="en" id="top-CreateModule">

    <title>Create a Module</title>

    <body>

        <section id="diffways">
            <p>You can produce a module in different ways:
                <ul>
                    <li>Create an entire module from scratch. For very simple modules, you can use the <xref format="dita" href="/dev/CreatingModules/Create-With-Module-Creator.html">DNN Module Creator</xref>.</li>

                    <li>Start with module development templates, such as:
                        <ul>
                            <li><xref format="dita" href="https://github.com/dnnsoftware/DNN.Templates/releases">DNN 8 Templates</xref></li>
                            <li><xref format="dita" href="https://github.com/ChrisHammond/DNNTemplates">Chris Hammond's DotNetNuke Module and Theme Development Templates</xref> (<xref format="dita" href="http://www.chrishammond.com/blog/itemid/2616/using-the-new-module-development-templates-for-dot">Installation instructions</xref>)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>

                    <li>Customize a pre-existing module.
                        <ph conref="../../common/bptext/bp-3rdPartyExtensions.html" />
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section id="diffprogfws">
            <p>You can also use different programming frameworks (Web Forms, MVC, SPA) and languages (C#, VB) to create your module.</p>
        </section>

    </body>


